            <p>138 Durocher Street<lb/>
                Montreal&#44; March 25th&#44; 1892.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Pray accept the assurance<lb/> of my heartfelt sympathy in your<lb/> sorrow at the death of your dear<lb/> grandchild.  A devoted lover of<lb/> children myself&#44; I feel deeply for<lb/> those who suffer the pang which<lb/> their loss occasions.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have not the honor of knowing<lb/> your daughter and son&#45;in&#45;law&#44; but<lb/> would ask you to convey to them<lb/> my sincere condolence&#44; and my fervent<lb/> wish that our Heavenly Father may<lb/> vouchsafe to them many bright years<lb/>&#45;&#45;years unclouded by sorrow and trouble.<lb/></p>
            <p>My wife unites with me in this<lb/> expression of heartfelt sympathy.<lb/></p>
            <p>With kind regards and best<lb/> wishes&#44; I remain<lb/> Very truly yours<lb/> Meldola de Sola<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. Morais<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
